snippet: The ruling party of President José Eduardo dos Santos received nearly three-quarters of the votes cast on Friday after 60 percent of the ballots had been counted, electoral officials said.
abstract: Angola's governing party, despite widespread discontent over inequality and corruption, is poised to sweep the parliamentary elections, winning over three-quarters of the votes cast; victory will ensure President Jose Eduardo dos Santos a five-year extension to his 33 years at the country’s helm.
lead_paragraph: The ruling party of President José Eduardo dos Santos received nearly three-quarters of the votes cast on Friday after 60 percent of the ballots had been counted, electoral officials said.
